 Color coordinates  Slate gray is a gray color with a slight azure tinge that is a representation of the average color of the material slate. The first recorded use of slate gray as a color name in English was in 1705.[1]   Color coordinates  Displayed at right is the web color light slate gray.  Color coordinates  Displayed at right is the web color dark slate gray. Computers 
